    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="793"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d793">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/22706b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-22">April 22,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I enclose memorandum from Berle<note n="57" xml:id="d793fn57">Not printed.</note>
                    and Welles<note n="58" xml:id="d793fn58">Dated April 17, <ref target="#pg_903"
                            >p. 903</ref>.</note> in regard to asking the Philippine Commonwealth to
                    become a signer of the United Nations Pact. Frankly, I hesitate to do this at
                    this time. I spoke to Tom Connally<note n="59" xml:id="d793fn59">Chairman of the
                        Senate Committee on Foreign Relations.</note> about it and he agrees with
                    me.</p>
                <p>I am, of course, a firm believer in carrying through our promise of independence
                    to the Philippines, but I do not think we should modify the present law by a
                    step which might be considered to hold out a promise to them for immediate
                    independence if, for example, the war were to terminate early in 1943. There
                    might be a period of repair and adjustment for two or three years for which the
                    United States should be responsible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>P.S. Please return enclosures for my files.<note n="60" xml:id="d793fn60"
                            >Enclosures were returned by the Secretary with a covering memorandum of
                            July 2.</note>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
